Bandits in the early hours of Thursday attacked Daddarar villages in the Jibia Local Government Area of Katsina State and killed six people, including the village head. A source told DAILY POST that five persons were also abducted by the bandits during the attack. The source explained that at Daddarar Liman, the bandits killed the village head, Alhaji Jafaru Rabiu, popularly known as Magaji Yangayya, alongside his house help, Malam Mansir Danye. “Here in the main Daddarar village, they killed four people and also abducted some, altogether, they killed six people and abducted five,” he said. He explained that among the abductees was also a maid who was about to get married, saying that several other people sustained injuries during the attack including his neighbours. According to him, the attackers conducted a house-to-house search where they carted away animals and collected other valuables, including money, from residents without the presence of security personnel. The source stated that the Divisional Police Officer (DPO) from Jibia was able to scare the attackers out of the villages. Confirming the incident, the Police Public Relations Officer in Katsina, SP Gambo Isah, explained that five people were killed, including the village head while one person is missing.